author: @dr.mikeybee
text: BTW, I use gTTS for text to speech.  It sounds better than the Linda Johnson voice, and it's fairly fast again.  You can also use ESPNet for an LJ voice if you want to run locally.  Remember to mute the microphone while you have the computer speak.  Also vosk does great STT if you don't have Jarvis.

author: @dr.mikeybee
text: You can add a big if then else loop in front of the chatbot; so if you ask for the time, for example, you can call that action.  If nothing is recognized, it goes to the chatbot model.

author: @Crayphor
text: Seems like the spam happens when you reach the edge of the line. It is trying to print the line and then flush the line over and over again but it doesn't realize that it is on a new line. Maybe there are functions which can say the size of a line in stdout and you could make some logic to only flush and reprint the part of the string that is in the last "line length" of stdout.
